HashSet in Java implements the Set interface of the Collections Framework. It is used to store the unique elements, and it doesn't maintain any specific order of elements.
a. HashSet does not allow duplicate elements.
b. Uses HashMap internally which is an implementation of hash table data structure.
c. Also implements Serializable and Cloneable interfaces.
d. HashSet is not thread-safe. To make it thread-safe, synchronization is needed externally.
e. Does not support primitive types directly; requires wrapper classes (Integer, Character, etc.).

